{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857418663,"sessionID":"ses_286a69499ffe42thtO1Jz8aHeX","part":{"id":"prt_d7959b76e001MlHs3uw5TuVj28","messageID":"msg_d7959abd6001OliLV3W904H4CN","sessionID":"ses_286a69499ffe42thtO1Jz8aHeX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_62b8dc52c15f407ea33e19b0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-012 — Session Storage Interface Definition Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-012 — Session Storage Interface Definition |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Atomic Tasks\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Interface Definition\n18: \n19: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Store` interface in `pkg/store/store.go`\n20:   - Method: `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n21:   - Method: `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n22:   - Method: `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n23:   - Method: `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n24:   - Method: `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n25:   - Method: `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n26:   - Method: `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n27:   - Method: `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error`\n28:   - Method: `Close() error`\n29: \n30: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `ErrNotFound` sentinel error in `pkg/store/store.go`\n31:   - Error message: `\"store: not found\"`\n32:   - Used when session key is absent on read\n33:   - Used when last-activity update targets missing session\n34: \n35: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define key pattern constants in `pkg/store/store.go`\n36:   - `sessionPrefix = \"session:\"`\n37:   - `expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"`\n38:   - `lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"`\n39: \n40: ### Phase 2: Singleton Pattern\n41: \n42: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n43:   - Define `provider Store` package variable\n44:   - Define `initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}`\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `Storage()` function in `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n47:   - Calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`\n48:   - Returns `provider` instance\n49:   - Thread-safe singleton access\n50: \n51: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `initStore()` function in `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n52:   - Read `STORE_TYPE` environment variable (case-insensitive)\n53:   - Default to `\"redis\"` if unset\n54:   - Validate: only `\"redis\"` or `\"valkey\"` allowed\n55:   - Call `makeRedisOptions()` or `makeValkeyOptions()` based on type\n56:   - Construct Redis or Valkey store instance\n57:   - Log fatal via `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)` on error\n58: \n59: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Define provider type constants in `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n60:   - `redisStoreType = \"redis\"`\n61:   - `valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"`\n62: \n63: ### Phase 3: Redis Implementation\n64: \n65: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/store/store_redis.go`\n66:   - Define `redisStore` struct with fields:\n67:     - `cli *redisv9.Client` (from `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`)\n68:     - `sessionPrefix string`\n69:     - `expiryIndexKey string`\n70:     - `lastActivityIndexKey string`\n71: \n72: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `makeRedisOptions()` function\n73:   - Read `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable (required)\n74:   - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD` environment variable\n75:   - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` (default `\"true\"`, case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"`)\n76:   - Return `*redisv9.Options` with `Addr` and `Password`\n77:   - Error if `REDIS_ADDR` empty or password required but empty\n78: \n79: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `NewRedisStore()` constructor\n80:   - Takes `*redisv9.Options`\n81:   - Creates Redis client\n82:   - Returns `&redisStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"...\", expiryIndexKey: \"...\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"...\"}`\n83: \n84: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `redisStore.Ping()` method\n85:   - Execute `PING` command\n86:   - Expect string response `\"PONG\"`\n87:   - Return error if not PONG\n88: \n89: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `redisStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` method\n90:   - Construct key: `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n91:   - Execute `GET` command\n92:   - If `redis.Nil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n93:   - Unmarshal JSON to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n94:   - Return error on unmarshal failure\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `redisStore.StoreSandbox()` method\n97:   - Validate: sandbox not nil, `ExpiresAt` not zero\n98:   - Construct session key\n99:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n100:   - Use Pipeline for atomic operations:\n101:     - `SETNX` session key with JSON\n102:     - `ZADD expiryIndexKey` with score=`ExpiresAt.Unix()`, member=sessionID\n103:     - `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score=`time.Now().Unix()`, member=sessionID\n104:   - Execute pipeline\n105:   - Return error if any command fails\n106: \n107: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `redisStore.UpdateSandbox()` method\n108:   - Construct session key\n109:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n110:   - Execute `SET key value XX` (key must exist)\n111:   - If key not exists → return error\n112:   - Do NOT modify ZSET entries\n113: \n114: - [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `redisStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` method\n115:   - Construct session key\n116:   - Use Pipeline for atomic operations:\n117:     - `DEL` session key\n118:     - `ZREM expiryIndexKey` member=sessionID\n119:     - `ZREM lastActivityIndexKey` member=sessionID\n120:   - Execute pipeline\n121:   - Return error on failure\n122: \n123: - [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `redisStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` method\n124:   - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n125:   - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE expiryIndexKey -inf before.Unix() LIMIT 0 limit`\n126:   - Get session IDs from result\n127:   - Pipeline `GET` for each session key\n128:   - Unmarshal JSON, skip missing keys (tolerate orphaned ZSET members)\n129:   - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **TASK-029**: Implement `redisStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()` method\n132:   - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n133:   - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE lastActivityIndexKey -inf before.Unix() LIMIT 0 limit`\n134:   - Get session IDs from result\n135:   - Pipeline `GET` for each session key\n136:   - Unmarshal JSON, skip missing keys\n137:   - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n138: \n139: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `redisStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` method\n140:   - Validate: sessionID non-empty\n141:   - If `at` is zero time → use `time.Now()`\n142:   - Construct session key\n143:   - Execute `GET` to verify key exists\n144:   - If not exists → return `ErrNotFound`\n145:   - Execute `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score=`at.Unix()`, member=sessionID\n146:   - Return error on failure\n147: \n148: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `redisStore.Close()` method\n149:   - Call `cli.Close()`\n150:   - Return error\n151: \n152: ### Phase 4: Valkey Implementation\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n155:   - Define `valkeyStore` struct with fields:\n156:     - `cli valkey.Client` (from `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`)\n157:     - `sessionPrefix string`\n158:     - `expiryIndexKey string`\n159:     - `lastActivityIndexKey string`\n160: \n161: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` function\n162:   - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable (required, comma-separated)\n163:   - Split by `,` → `InitAddress` slice\n164:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variable\n165:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` (default `\"true\"`)\n166:   - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, if true → `DisableCache=true`)\n167:   - Read `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, if true → `ForceSingleClient=true`)\n168:   - Return `*valkey.ClientOption`\n169:   - Error if `VALKEY_ADDR` empty or password required but empty\n170: \n171: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `NewValkeyStore()` constructor\n172:   - Takes `*valkey.ClientOption`\n173:   - Create Valkey client\n174:   - Returns `&valkeyStore{cli: client, ...}`\n175: \n176: - [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `valkeyStore.Ping()` method\n177:   - Execute `B().Ping()`\n178:   - Expect string response `\"PONG\"`\n179: \n180: - [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` method\n181:   - Construct key: `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n182:   - Execute `B().Get().Key(key)`\n183:   - If `IsValkeyNil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n184:   - Unmarshal bytes to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n185: \n186: - [ ] **TASK-045**: Implement `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` method\n187:   - Validate: sandbox not nil, `ExpiresAt` not zero\n188:   - Construct session key\n189:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n190:   - Use `DoMulti` for atomic operations:\n191:     - `SETNX` session key with JSON\n192:     - `ZADD expiryIndexKey` with score, member\n193:     - `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score, member\n194:   - Check all responses for errors\n195: \n196: - [ ] **TASK-046**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` method\n197:   - Construct session key\n198:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n199:   - Execute `SET key value XX`\n200:   - Success requires response `ToString() == \"OK\"`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **TASK-047**: Implement `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` method\n203:   - Construct session key\n204:   - Use `DoMulti`:\n205:     - `DEL` session key\n206:     - `ZREM expiryIndexKey` member\n207:     - `ZREM lastActivityIndexKey` member\n208: \n209: - [ ] **TASK-048**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` method\n210:   - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n211:   - Execute `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)`\n212:   - Get session IDs\n213:   - Use `Mget` to load all session keys (comment: keys should be in same slot)\n214:   - Unmarshal JSON, skip empty strings\n215: \n216: - [ ] **TASK-049**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()` method\n217:   - Same as `ListExpiredSandboxes` but on `lastActivityIndexKey`\n218: \n219: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` method\n220:   - Validate: sessionID non-empty\n221:   - If `at` is zero → use `time.Now()`\n222:   - Execute `Exists` key → must return 1\n223:   - If 0 → return `ErrNotFound`\n224:   - Execute `Zadd` with timestamp\n225: \n226: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `valkeyStore.Close()` method\n227:   - Call `vs.cli.Close()`\n228:   - Return nil\n229: \n230: ### Phase 5: Helper Functions\n231: \n232: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Implement `sessionKey(sessionID string)` helper\n233:   - Returns `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n234: \n235: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement `marshalSandboxInfo(info *types.SandboxInfo)` helper\n236:   - Marshal to JSON string\n237:   - Return error on failure\n238: \n239: - [ ] **TASK-062**: Implement `unmarshalSandboxInfo(data string, info *types.SandboxInfo)` helper\n240:   - Unmarshal from JSON string\n241:   - Return error on failure\n242: \n243: ### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n244: \n245: #### Unit Tests - Interface Contract\n246: \n247: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_test.go`\n248:   - Test `ErrNotFound` error message equals `\"store: not found\"`\n249: \n250: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Test `sessionKey()` function\n251:   - Given: sessionID `\"abc\"`\n252:   - When: `sessionKey(\"abc\")` called\n253:   - Then: returns `\"session:abc\"`\n254: \n255: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Test `marshalSandboxInfo()` with valid sandbox\n256:   - Given: valid `*types.SandboxInfo`\n257:   - When: marshaled\n258:   - Then: returns valid JSON string\n259: \n260: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Test `unmarshalSandboxInfo()` with valid JSON\n261:   - Given: valid JSON string\n262:   - When: unmarshaled\n263:   - Then: returns `*types.SandboxInfo` with correct fields\n264: \n265: - [ ] **TEST-005**: Test `unmarshalSandboxInfo()` with invalid JSON\n266:   - Given: invalid JSON string\n267:   - When: unmarshaled\n268:   - Then: returns error\n269: \n270: #### Unit Tests - Redis Implementation\n271: \n272: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go`\n273:   - Test `makeRedisOptions()` with all env vars set\n274: \n275: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Test `makeRedisOptions()` with missing `REDIS_ADDR`\n276:   - Given: `REDIS_ADDR` not set\n277:   - When: `makeRedisOptions()` called\n278:   - Then: returns error\n279: \n280: - [ ] **TEST-012**: Test `makeRedisOptions()` with password required but empty\n281:   - Given: `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n282:   - When: `makeRedisOptions()` called\n283:   - Then: returns error\n284: \n285: - [ ] **TEST-013**: Test `makeRedisOptions()` with `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n286:   - Given: `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"`\n287:   - When: `makeRedisOptions()` called\n288:   - Then: returns options with empty password\n289: \n290: - [ ] **TEST-014**: Mock test `redisStore.Ping()` returns PONG\n291:   - Given: mocked Redis client returning PONG\n292:   - When: `Ping()` called\n293:   - Then: returns nil error\n294: \n295: - [ ] **TEST-015**: Mock test `redisStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` with missing key\n296:   - Given: mocked Redis returning `redis.Nil`\n297:   - When: `GetSandboxBySessionID()` called\n298:   - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n299: \n300: - [ ] **TEST-016**: Mock test `redisStore.StoreSandbox()` with nil sandbox\n301:   - Given: `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n302:   - When: called\n303:   - Then: returns error\n304: \n305: - [ ] **TEST-017**: Mock test `redisStore.StoreSandbox()` pipeline atomicity\n306:   - Given: valid sandbox\n307:   - When: `StoreSandbox()` called\n308:   - Then: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity all called\n309: \n310: - [ ] **TEST-018**: Mock test `redisStore.UpdateSandbox()` with missing key\n311:   - Given: mocked Redis returning empty from SET XX\n312:   - When: `UpdateSandbox()` called\n313:   - Then: returns error\n314: \n315: - [ ] **TEST-019**: Mock test `redisStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` pipeline\n316:   - Given: existing session\n317:   - When: `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` called\n318:   - Then: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity all called\n319: \n320: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Mock test `redisStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` with limit 0\n321:   - Given: `limit = 0`\n322:   - When: `ListExpiredSandboxes()` called\n323:   - Then: returns `nil, nil`\n324: \n325: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Mock test `redisStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` tolerates orphaned keys\n326:   - Given: ZSET returns IDs but some GET return nil\n327:   - When: `ListExpiredSandboxes()` called\n328:   - Then: skips missing keys, returns found ones\n329: \n330: - [ ] **TEST-022**: Mock test `redisStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with missing session\n331:   - Given: mocked Redis returning `redis.Nil` on GET\n332:   - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n333:   - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n334: \n335: - [ ] **TEST-023**: Mock test `redisStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with zero time\n336:   - Given: `at = time.Time{}`\n337:   - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n338:   - Then: uses `time.Now()` for ZADD score\n339: \n340: #### Unit Tests - Valkey Implementation\n341: \n342: - [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n343:   - Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with all env vars set\n344: \n345: - [ ] **TEST-031**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with missing `VALKEY_ADDR`\n346:   - Given: `VALKEY_ADDR` not set\n347:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n348:   - Then: returns error\n349: \n350: - [ ] **TEST-032**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with comma-separated addresses\n351:   - Given: `VALKEY_ADDR=\"addr1,addr2,addr3\"`\n352:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n353:   - Then: `InitAddress = [\"addr1\", \"addr2\", \"addr3\"]`\n354: \n355: - [ ] **TEST-033**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n356:   - Given: `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\"`\n357:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n358:   - Then: `DisableCache=true`\n359: \n360: - [ ] **TEST-034**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n361:   - Given: `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"`\n362:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n363:   - Then: `ForceSingleClient=true`\n364: \n365: - [ ] **TEST-035**: Mock test `valkeyStore.Ping()` returns PONG\n366: \n367: - [ ] **TEST-036**: Mock test `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` with missing key\n368:   - Given: `IsValkeyNil` true\n369:   - When: `GetSandboxBySessionID()` called\n370:   - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n371: \n372: - [ ] **TEST-037**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` DoMulti atomicity\n373: \n374: - [ ] **TEST-038**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n375:   - Given: SET XX returns not \"OK\"\n376:   - When: `UpdateSandbox()` called\n377:   - Then: returns error\n378: \n379: - [ ] **TEST-039**: Mock test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` MGET optimization\n380: \n381: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` Exists check\n382:   - Given: Exists returns 0\n383:   - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n384:   - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n385: \n386: #### Unit Tests - Singleton\n387: \n388: - [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `pkg/store/singleton_test.go`\n389:   - Test `Storage()` returns same instance on multiple calls\n390: \n391: - [ ] **TEST-051**: Test `Storage()` thread safety\n392:   - Given: 100 goroutines calling `Storage()` concurrently\n393:   - When: all run\n394:   - Then: `initStore` executes exactly once, all get same instance\n395: \n396: - [ ] **TEST-052**: Test `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE` unset\n397:   - Given: `STORE_TYPE` not set\n398:   - When: `initStore()` called\n399:   - Then: creates Redis store\n400: \n401: - [ ] **TEST-053**: Test `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE=redis` (case-insensitive)\n402:   - Given: `STORE_TYPE=\"REDIS\"`\n403:   - When: `initStore()` called\n404:   - Then: creates Redis store\n405: \n406: - [ ] **TEST-054**: Test `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n407:   - Given: `STORE_TYPE=\"VALKEY\"`\n408:   - When: `initStore()` called\n409:   - Then: creates Valkey store\n410: \n411: - [ ] **TEST-055**: Test `initStore()` with invalid `STORE_TYPE`\n412:   - Given: `STORE_TYPE=\"invalid\"`\n413:   - When: `initStore()` called\n414:   - Then: logs fatal error\n415: \n416: #### Integration Tests - Redis\n417: \n418: - [ ] **TEST-060**: Create `pkg/store/store_redis_integration_test.go`\n419:   - Requires Docker Redis or testcontainers\n420: \n421: - [ ] **TEST-061**: Integration test `redisStore.Ping()` with real Redis\n422: \n423: - [ ] **TEST-062**: Integration test `redisStore.StoreSandbox()` → `GetSandboxBySessionID()`\n424:   - Store sandbox\n425:   - Retrieve by session ID\n426:   - Verify fields match\n427: \n428: - [ ] **TEST-063**: Integration test `redisStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n429:   - Store sandbox\n430:   - Update sandbox\n431:   - Verify updated fields\n432:   - Try update non-existent → expect error\n433: \n434: - [ ] **TEST-064**: Integration test `redisStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` cleanup\n435:   - Store sandbox\n436:   - Delete\n437:   - Verify GET returns `ErrNotFound`\n438:   - Verify ZSETs don't contain session ID\n439: \n440: - [ ] **TEST-065**: Integration test `redisStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()`\n441:   - Store multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n442:   - Query with `before` time\n443:   - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n444: \n445: - [ ] **TEST-066**: Integration test `redisStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n446:   - Store multiple sandboxes, update some with `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n447:   - Query with `before` time\n448:   - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n449: \n450: - [ ] **TEST-067**: Integration test ZSET index consistency under concurrent operations\n451:   - Multiple goroutines Store/Delete concurrently\n452:   - Verify ZSET indices remain consistent\n453: \n454: #### Integration Tests - Valkey\n455: \n456: - [ ] **TEST-070**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_integration_test.go`\n457:   - Requires Docker Valkey or testcontainers\n458: \n459: - [ ] **TEST-071**: Integration test `valkeyStore.Ping()` with real Valkey\n460: \n461: - [ ] **TEST-072**: Integration test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` → `GetSandboxBySessionID()`\n462: \n463: - [ ] **TEST-073**: Integration test `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` cleanup\n464: \n465: - [ ] **TEST-074**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()`\n466: \n467: - [ ] **TEST-075**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n468: \n469: ### Phase 7: Documentation\n470: \n471: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/store/doc.go`\n472:   - Package overview\n473:   - Store interface contract\n474:   - Redis and Valkey backend support\n475:   - Singleton access pattern\n476:   - Configuration via environment variables\n477: \n478: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to `Store` interface methods\n479:   - Document parameters and return values\n480:   - Document error conditions\n481:   - Include `ErrNotFound` semantics\n482: \n483: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Add godoc comments to `redisStore` methods\n484:   - Document Redis command patterns used\n485:   - Document pipeline atomicity\n486: \n487: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add godoc comments to `valkeyStore` methods\n488:   - Document Valkey API patterns used\n489:   - Document DoMulti atomicity\n490: \n491: - [ ] **DOC-005**: Document key patterns in code comments\n492:   - `session:{id}` for JSON storage\n493:   - `session:expiry` ZSET for expiry index\n494:   - `session:last_activity` ZSET for activity index\n495: \n496: - [ ] **DOC-006**: Document ZSET score semantics\n497:   - Expiry score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n498:   - Last activity score = `LastActivityAt.Unix()`\n499: \n500: - [ ] **DOC-007**: Document environment variables in `README.md` or code comments\n501:   - All `REDIS_*` variables\n502:   - All `VALKEY_*` variables\n503:   - `STORE_TYPE` selection\n504:   - Default values and required status\n505: \n506: - [ ] **DOC-008**: Add example usage in doc.go or example test\n507:   - Initialize store via `Storage()`\n508:   - Call `Ping()` to verify connectivity\n509:   - Call `StoreSandbox()` to persist sandbox\n510:   - Call `GetSandboxBySessionID()` to retrieve\n511: \n512: ---\n513: \n514: ## Acceptance Criteria\n515: \n516: - [ ] `Store` interface matches exact signatures from design spec\n517: - [ ] `ErrNotFound` error returned consistently for missing sessions\n518: - [ ] Redis implementation uses `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n519: - [ ] Valkey implementation uses `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n520: - [ ] `Storage()` singleton initializes exactly once under concurrent access\n521: - [ ] Provider selection respects `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitivity\n522: - [ ] Default provider is `redis` when `STORE_TYPE` unset\n523: - [ ] Password-optional mode works for both backends\n524: - [ ] ZSET indices remain consistent after store/update/delete operations\n525: - [ ] `StoreSandbox()` uses pipeline/DoMulti for atomic index updates\n526: - [ ] `UpdateSandbox()` uses SET XX semantics (key must exist)\n527: - [ ] `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` removes key and ZSET members atomically\n528: - [ ] `ListExpiredSandboxes()` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry index\n529: - [ ] `ListInactiveSandboxes()` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity index\n530: - [ ] List methods tolerate orphaned ZSET members (skip missing keys)\n531: - [ ] `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` verifies key exists before ZADD\n532: - [ ] All environment variables documented and tested\n533: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n534: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Redis and Valkey\n535: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n536: \n537: ---\n538: \n539: ## Dependencies\n540: \n541: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n542: |------------|--------|-------|\n543: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | External | Redis client library |\n544: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | External | Valkey client library |\n545: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n546: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | `SandboxInfo` type |\n547: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types` | Internal | SandboxInfo alias source |\n548: \n549: ---\n550: \n551: ## Implementation Order\n552: \n553: ```\n554: TASK-001 → TASK-002 → TASK-003\n555:               ↓\n556: TASK-010 → TASK-011 → TASK-012 → TASK-013\n557:               ↓\n558: TASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-022 → TASK-023 → ... → TASK-031\n559:               ↓\n560: TASK-040 → TASK-041 → TASK-042 → TASK-043 → ... → TASK-051\n561:               ↓\n562: TASK-060 → TASK-061 → TASK-062\n563:               ↓\n564: TEST-001 → ... → TEST-075\n565:               ↓\n566: DOC-001 → ... → DOC-008\n567: ```\n\n(End of file - total 567 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-012 — Session Storage Interface Definition Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-012 — Session Storage Interface Definition |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Interface Definition\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Store` interface in `pkg/store/store.go`\n  - Method: `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775857418638,"end":1775857418660}}}}
