{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857436830,"sessionID":"ses_286a69499ffe42thtO1Jz8aHeX","part":{"id":"prt_d795a022c0015N43DrHiUIgPje","messageID":"msg_d7959f2c8001RXBF2ZezCF6skR","sessionID":"ses_286a69499ffe42thtO1Jz8aHeX","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_9229ab5376fd4eddb6f18579","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/src","description":"List AR-014/src directory contents"},"output":"total 8\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 11 05:35 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 root root 4096 Apr 11 05:37 ..\n","metadata":{"output":"total 8\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 11 05:35 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 root root 4096 Apr 11 05:37 ..\n","exit":0,"description":"List AR-014/src directory contents","truncated":false},"title":"List AR-014/src directory contents","time":{"start":1775857436817,"end":1775857436829}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857436835,"sessionID":"ses_286a69499ffe42thtO1Jz8aHeX","part":{"id":"prt_d7959fc4b0019NmLAfX4Jjus5w","messageID":"msg_d7959f2c8001RXBF2ZezCF6skR","sessionID":"ses_286a69499ffe42thtO1Jz8aHeX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_21b3db0770e04c1d985856d3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: Valkey Storage Implementation (AR-014)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement the Valkey backend for the session storage interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage with indexed queries for garbage collection based on expiry and last-activity timestamps.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: The Valkey storage implementation provides an alternative backend for session persistence in the agentcube project. It enables:\n12: \n13: 1. **Session persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox information using Valkey key-value storage\n14: 2. **Garbage collection support**: Maintain sorted set indices for expiry and last-activity based cleanup\n15: 3. **Deployment flexibility**: Valkey offers Apache 2.0 licensing and enhanced performance characteristics\n16: 4. **Atomic operations**: Use Valkey `DoMulti` to ensure consistent index updates\n17: 5. **Cluster awareness**: Support for comma-separated addresses and cluster-specific options\n18: \n19: This implementation is the focus of AR-014 and builds upon the interface defined in AR-012, running in parallel with the Redis implementation from AR-013.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Scope\n24: \n25: ### In Scope\n26: \n27: - `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Valkey implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n28: - `sessionKey()` helper function for consistent key construction (shared with Redis)\n29: - `makeValkeyOptions()` for environment variable parsing and client configuration\n30: - All `Store` interface methods implemented with Valkey fluent API\n31: - `DoMulti` operations for atomic multi-command operations\n32: - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper using MGET optimization\n33: - Unit tests with mocked Valkey client\n34: - Integration tests with real Valkey instance (Docker-based)\n35: \n36: ### Out of Scope\n37: \n38: - Redis implementation (covered in AR-013)\n39: - Alternative storage backends (etcd, Consul, etc.)\n40: - Valkey cluster sharding strategies beyond basic comma-separated addresses\n41: - Connection pooling tuning beyond default settings\n42: - Valkey-specific features beyond standard Redis-compatible commands\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## Impact Analysis\n47: \n48: ### Dependencies\n49: \n50: | Package | Purpose |\n51: |---------|---------|\n52: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library |\n53: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging for client options |\n54: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` type definitions |\n55: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Store interface (from AR-012) |\n56: \n57: ### Affected Components\n58: \n59: 1. **Sandbox Orchestrator**: Will use `Storage()` to persist sandbox metadata\n60: 2. **Garbage Collector**: Will use `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` for cleanup operations\n61: 3. **Session Manager**: Will use `UpdateSessionLastActivity` for activity tracking\n62: 4. **Configuration System**: Must provide `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variables when `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n63: \n64: ### Backward Compatibility\n65: \n66: - This is a new implementation of an existing interface\n67: - No breaking changes to the `Store` interface\n68: - Configuration via environment variables (no config file changes)\n69: - Transparent backend swapping via `STORE_TYPE` environment variable\n70: \n71: ### Risk Assessment\n72: \n73: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n74: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n75: | Valkey connection failures | Medium | High | `Ping()` method for health checks; connection retry in client library |\n76: | ZSET index inconsistency | Low | High | Atomic `DoMulti` operations ensure all-or-nothing updates |\n77: | Password misconfiguration | Medium | High | Clear error messages; `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` escape hatch |\n78: | Memory bloat from orphaned ZSET members | Low | Medium | List methods tolerate missing keys; periodic cleanup recommended |\n79: | Cluster slot conflicts in MGET | Low | Medium | Document in code comment; use `ForceSingleClient` option if needed |\n80: | Cache inconsistency | Low | Low | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` option for cache bypass |\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## Alternatives Considered\n85: \n86: ### Alternative 1: Reuse Redis Implementation\n87: \n88: **Approach**: Use the same client library for both Redis and Valkey\n89: \n90: **Pros**:\n91: - Less code duplication\n92: - Simpler dependency management\n93: \n94: **Cons**:\n95: - Valkey-specific optimizations not possible\n96: - `valkey-go` library provides better cluster support\n97: - Misses Valkey's enhanced features\n98: \n99: **Decision**: Use dedicated `valkey-go` client library for better Valkey-specific support.\n100: \n101: ### Alternative 2: Hash-Based Storage\n102: \n103: **Approach**: Store session data as Valkey Hash instead of JSON string\n104: \n105: **Pros**:\n106: - Partial field updates without full serialization\n107: - More efficient for small field changes\n108: - Native Valkey/Redis type\n109: \n110: **Cons**:\n111: - Complex nested structures (`EntryPoints` array) awkward in hashes\n112: - JSON marshaling already required for `SandboxInfo` type\n113: - Less portable if switching to other backends\n114: \n115: **Decision**: Use JSON string storage for simplicity and consistency.\n116: \n117: ### Alternative 3: TTL-Only Expiration\n118: \n119: **Approach**: Rely solely on Valkey native TTL instead of maintaining `session:expiry` ZSET\n120: \n121: **Pros**:\n122: - Simpler implementation\n123: - Automatic expiration handled by Valkey\n124: - Reduced memory footprint\n125: \n126: **Cons**:\n127: - Cannot efficiently query \"sessions expiring before time X\"\n128: - Last-activity tracking still requires ZSET\n129: - Inconsistent semantics between expiry and activity indices\n130: \n131: **Decision**: Maintain explicit ZSET indices for efficient range queries required by garbage collection.\n132: \n133: ### Alternative 4: Lua Script for Atomicity\n134: \n135: **Approach**: Use Lua scripts for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` instead of `DoMulti`\n136: \n137: **Pros**:\n138: - True atomic execution on Valkey server\n139: - Reduced network round trips\n140: \n141: **Cons**:\n142: - More complex code and debugging\n143: - Harder to test and maintain\n144: - `DoMulti` provides sufficient atomicity for this use case\n145: \n146: **Decision**: Use Valkey `DoMulti` for better code clarity and easier testing.\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## Implementation Details\n151: \n152: ### Valkey Store Structure\n153: \n154: ```go\n155: type valkeyStore struct {\n156:     cli                  valkey.Client\n157:     sessionPrefix        string\n158:     expiryIndexKey       string\n159:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### Key Patterns\n164: \n165: | Purpose | Key Pattern |\n166: |---------|-------------|\n167: | Session data | `session:{sessionId}` |\n168: | Expiry index | `session:expiry` |\n169: | Last activity index | `session:last_activity` |\n170: \n171: ### Connection Configuration\n172: \n173: ```go\n174: func makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n175:     valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n176:     if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n177:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n178:     }\n179:     \n180:     valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n181:     passwordRequired := true\n182:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.EqualFold(v, \"false\") {\n183:         passwordRequired = false\n184:     }\n185:     \n186:     if passwordRequired && valkeyPassword == \"\" {\n187:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n188:     }\n189:     \n190:     valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n191:         InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n192:         Password:    valkeyPassword,\n193:     }\n194:     \n195:     // Optional flags\n196:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n197:         if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n198:             valkeyClientOptions.DisableCache = true\n199:         }\n200:     }\n201:     \n202:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n203:         if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n204:             valkeyClientOptions.ForceSingleClient = true\n205:         }\n206:     }\n207:     \n208:     if valkeyClientOptions.DisableCache || valkeyClientOptions.ForceSingleClient {\n209:         klog.Infof(\"Valkey client options: DisableCache=%v, ForceSingleClient=%v\",\n210:             valkeyClientOptions.DisableCache, valkeyClientOptions.ForceSingleClient)\n211:     }\n212:     \n213:     return valkeyClientOptions, nil\n214: }\n215: ```\n216: \n217: ### Method Implementation Summary\n218: \n219: | Method | Valkey API | Notes |\n220: |--------|------------|-------|\n221: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string | Expect `PONG` response |\n222: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes | Use `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n223: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD expiry`, `ZADD last_activity` | Validate non-nil and non-zero ExpiresAt |\n224: | `UpdateSandbox` | `B().Set().Key(key).Value(val).XX()` | Response must equal \"OK\" |\n225: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` | Clean up all references |\n226: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(before.Unix)`, `Limit(0, limit)` + MGET | Skip missing keys |\n227: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` on `last_activity` + MGET | Skip missing keys |\n228: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key (must be 1), then `Zadd` | Return `ErrNotFound` if missing |\n229: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` | Close Valkey connection |\n230: \n231: ### Atomicity Guarantees\n232: \n233: - `StoreSandbox`: `DoMulti` ensures all-or-nothing for SETNX + ZADD + ZADD\n234: - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`: `DoMulti` ensures all-or-nothing for DEL + ZREM + ZREM\n235: - `UpdateSandbox`: Single `SET XX` command is atomic\n236: \n237: ### Error Handling\n238: \n239: - `IsValkeyNil()` → `store.ErrNotFound`\n240: - Connection errors → wrapped with context\n241: - `DoMulti` errors → fail fast with descriptive message\n242: - Type conversion errors → explicit error message\n243: \n244: ### ZSET Score Semantics\n245: \n246: | Index | Score Source |\n247: |-------|--------------|\n248: | `session:expiry` | `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store |\n249: | `session:last_activity` | `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on store; `float64(at.Unix())` on update |\n250: \n251: ### MGET Optimization\n252: \n253: The `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper function:\n254: - Builds all `session:{id}` keys from ZSET results\n255: - Uses single `Mget` command for batch retrieval\n256: - **Note**: Keys should be in same slot for cluster deployments (documented in code comment)\n257: - Skips entries where MGET returns empty string (orphaned ZSET members)\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Configuration Reference\n262: \n263: ### Environment Variables\n264: \n265: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n266: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n267: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated addresses (e.g., `host1:6379,host2:6379`) |\n268: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n269: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive boolean |\n270: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `\"true\"` to enable `DisableCache` |\n271: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `\"true\"` to enable `ForceSingleClient` |\n272: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `valkey` (case-insensitive) for this implementation |\n273: \n274: ---\n275: \n276: ## Testing Strategy\n277: \n278: ### Unit Tests\n279: \n280: 1. **TestValkeyStore_Ping_Success**: Mock `Ping` returns `PONG`\n281: 2. **TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound**: Mock `Get` returns nil\n282: 3. **TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected**: Validate input validation\n283: 4. **TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Success**: Verify `DoMulti` commands\n284: 5. **TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey**: Verify `SET XX` behavior\n285: 6. **TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID_Success**: Verify cleanup\n286: 7. **TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_Empty**: Limit <= 0 returns nil\n287: 8. **TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound**: Missing session\n288: 9. **TestValkeyStore_MGET_ToleratesMissingKeys**: Orphaned ZSET members skipped\n289: \n290: ### Integration Tests\n291: \n292: 1. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full CRUD operations with real Valkey\n293: 2. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_ConcurrentAccess**: Concurrent store/update/delete\n294: 3. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_IndexConsistency**: Verify ZSET consistency after operations\n295: 4. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_PasswordAuth**: Test with password authentication\n296: 5. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_ClusterAddresses**: Test comma-separated address parsing\n297: \n298: ### Test Fixtures\n299: \n300: ```go\n301: func newTestValkeyStore() (*valkeyStore, func()) {\n302:     // Use testcontainers-go or dockertest for Valkey container\n303:     // Return cleanup function\n304: }\n305: ```\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## Acceptance Criteria\n310: \n311: - [ ] `valkeyStore` struct implements all `Store` interface methods\n312: - [ ] Key patterns match spec: `session:`, `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`\n313: - [ ] `DoMulti` operations used for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n314: - [ ] `ErrNotFound` returned consistently for missing sessions (via `IsValkeyNil`)\n315: - [ ] Environment variable parsing matches spec table\n316: - [ ] `makeValkeyOptions()` validates required fields and optional flags\n317: - [ ] `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` uses MGET optimization\n318: - [ ] All unit tests pass with mocked client\n319: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance\n320: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for `store_valkey.go`\n321: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n322: - [ ] MGET cluster slot consideration documented in code comment\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ## References\n327: \n328: - Interface Definition: `session-store/design.md`\n329: - Specification: `session-store/spec.md`\n330: - AR-012 Proposal: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md` (base interface work)\n331: - AR-013 Proposal: `changes/AR-013/proposal.md` (Redis implementation)\n332: - Valkey Client Docs: https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n\n(End of file - total 332 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: Valkey Storage Implementation (AR-014)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the Valkey backend for the session storage interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage with indexed queries for garbage collection based on expiry and last-activity timestamps.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Valkey storage implementation provides an alternative backend for session persistence in the agentcube project. It enables:\n\n1. **Session persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox information using Valkey key-value storage\n2. **Garbage collection support**: Maintain sorted set indices for expiry and last-activity based cleanup\n3. **Deployment flexibility**: Valkey offers Apache 2.0 licensing and enhanced performance characteristics\n4. **Atomic operations**: Use Valkey `DoMulti` to ensure consistent index updates\n5. **Cluster awareness**: Support for comma-separated addresses and cluster-specific options\n\nThis implementation is the focus of AR-014 and builds upon the interface defined in AR-012, running in parallel with the Redis implementation from AR-013.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775857436811,"end":1775857436832}}}}
