{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857534874,"sessionID":"ses_286a69499ffe42thtO1Jz8aHeX","part":{"id":"prt_d795a7612001XoaOTSYtYasY7d","messageID":"msg_d795a62d0001VIsPWVAdNGWYEJ","sessionID":"ses_286a69499ffe42thtO1Jz8aHeX","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_78b4be49bd194665bf3f8e38","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","content":"# AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Valkey Store Structure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n  - Define `valkeyStore` struct with fields:\n    - `cli valkey.Client` (from `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`)\n    - `sessionPrefix string`\n    - `expiryIndexKey string`\n    - `lastActivityIndexKey string`\n\n### Phase 2: Connection Configuration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` function\n  - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable (required, comma-separated)\n  - Split by `,` → `InitAddress` slice\n  - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variable\n  - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` (default `\"true\"`, case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"`)\n  - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, if true → `DisableCache=true`)\n  - Read `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, if true → `ForceSingleClient=true`)\n  - Return `*valkey.ClientOption`\n  - Error if `VALKEY_ADDR` empty or password required but empty\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewValkeyStore()` constructor\n  - Takes `*valkey.ClientOption`\n  - Creates Valkey client via `valkey.NewClient()`\n  - Returns `&valkeyStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"...\", expiryIndexKey: \"...\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"...\"}`\n  - Error on client creation failure\n\n### Phase 3: Core Store Methods\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `valkeyStore.Ping()` method\n  - Execute `B().Ping()` command\n  - Expect string response `\"PONG\"`\n  - Return error if not PONG\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` method\n  - Construct key: `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n  - Execute `B().Get().Key(key)`\n  - If `IsValkeyNil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n  - Unmarshal bytes to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n  - Return error on unmarshal failure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` method\n  - Validate: sandbox not nil, `ExpiresAt` not zero\n  - Construct session key\n  - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n  - Use `DoMulti` for atomic operations:\n    - `SETNX` session key with JSON\n    - `ZADD expiryIndexKey` with score=`ExpiresAt.Unix()`, member=sessionID\n    - `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score=`time.Now().Unix()`, member=sessionID\n  - Check all responses for errors\n  - Return error if SETNX fails (key already exists)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` method\n  - Construct session key\n  - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n  - Execute `B().Set().Key().Value().Xx()` (key must exist)\n  - If response != `\"OK\"` → return `ErrNotFound`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` method\n  - Construct session key\n  - Use `DoMulti`:\n    - `DEL` session key\n    - `ZREM expiryIndexKey` member=sessionID\n    - `ZREM lastActivityIndexKey` member=sessionID\n  - Check all responses for errors\n\n- [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` method\n  - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n  - Execute `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)`\n  - Get session IDs from result\n  - Call `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper\n  - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()` method\n  - Same as `ListExpiredSandboxes` but on `lastActivityIndexKey`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` method\n  - Validate: sessionID non-empty\n  - If `at` is zero time → use `time.Now()`\n  - Construct session key\n  - Execute `Exists` key → must return 1\n  - If 0 → return `ErrNotFound`\n  - Execute `Zadd` with timestamp score\n  - Return error on failure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `valkeyStore.Close()` method\n  - Call `vs.cli.Close()`\n  - Return nil\n\n### Phase 4: Helper Functions\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper\n  - Takes `[]string` session IDs\n  - Build all `session:{id}` keys\n  - Use single `Mget` command for batch retrieval\n  - Add code comment: \"Keys should be in same slot for cluster deployments\"\n  - Unmarshal JSON, skip empty strings (orphaned ZSET members)\n  - Log warnings via `klog.Warningf()` for orphaned/invalid entries\n  - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo, error`\n\n### Phase 5: Testing (TDD)\n\n#### Unit Tests - Configuration\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n  - Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with all env vars set\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with missing `VALKEY_ADDR`\n  - Given: `VALKEY_ADDR` not set\n  - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with comma-separated addresses\n  - Given: `VALKEY_ADDR=\"addr1,addr2,addr3\"`\n  - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n  - Then: `InitAddress = [\"addr1\", \"addr2\", \"addr3\"]`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n  - Given: `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\"`\n  - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n  - Then: `DisableCache=true`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n  - Given: `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"`\n  - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n  - Then: `ForceSingleClient=true`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-006**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with password required but empty\n  - Given: `VALKEY_PASSWORD` empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n  - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-007**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n  - Given: `VALKEY_PASSWORD` empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"`\n  - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n  - Then: returns options with empty password\n\n#### Unit Tests - Store Methods\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: Mock test `valkeyStore.Ping()` returns PONG\n  - Given: mocked Valkey client returning PONG\n  - When: `Ping()` called\n  - Then: returns nil error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: Mock test `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` with missing key\n  - Given: `IsValkeyNil` true\n  - When: `GetSandboxBySessionID()` called\n  - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-012**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` with nil sandbox\n  - Given: `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n  - When: called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-013**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` with zero ExpiresAt\n  - Given: sandbox with `ExpiresAt.IsZero() = true`\n  - When: called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-014**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` DoMulti atomicity\n  - Given: valid sandbox\n  - When: `StoreSandbox()` called\n  - Then: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity all called\n\n- [ ] **TEST-015**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n  - Given: SET XX returns not \"OK\"\n  - When: `UpdateSandbox()` called\n  - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-016**: Mock test `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` DoMulti\n  - Given: existing session\n  - When: `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` called\n  - Then: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity all called\n\n- [ ] **TEST-017**: Mock test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` with limit 0\n  - Given: `limit = 0`\n  - When: `ListExpiredSandboxes()` called\n  - Then: returns `nil, nil`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-018**: Mock test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` tolerates orphaned keys\n  - Given: ZSET returns IDs but some MGET return empty\n  - When: `ListExpiredSandboxes()` called\n  - Then: skips missing keys, returns found ones\n\n- [ ] **TEST-019**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with missing session\n  - Given: Exists returns 0\n  - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n  - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with zero time\n  - Given: `at = time.Time{}`\n  - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n  - Then: uses `time.Now()` for ZADD score\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with empty sessionID\n  - Given: `sessionID = \"\"`\n  - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n#### Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_integration_test.go`\n  - Requires Docker Valkey or testcontainers\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: Integration test `valkeyStore.Ping()` with real Valkey\n\n- [ ] **TEST-032**: Integration test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` → `GetSandboxBySessionID()`\n  - Store sandbox\n  - Retrieve by session ID\n  - Verify fields match\n\n- [ ] **TEST-033**: Integration test `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n  - Store sandbox\n  - Update sandbox\n  - Verify updated fields\n  - Try update non-existent → expect `ErrNotFound`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-034**: Integration test `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` cleanup\n  - Store sandbox\n  - Delete\n  - Verify GET returns `ErrNotFound`\n  - Verify ZSETs don't contain session ID\n\n- [ ] **TEST-035**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()`\n  - Store multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n  - Query with `before` time\n  - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-036**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n  - Store multiple sandboxes, update some with `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n  - Query with `before` time\n  - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-037**: Integration test ZSET index consistency under concurrent operations\n  - Multiple goroutines Store/Delete concurrently\n  - Verify ZSET indices remain consistent\n\n- [ ] **TEST-038**: Integration test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` full flow\n  - Store sandbox\n  - Update last activity\n  - Verify ZSET score updated\n\n- [ ] **TEST-039**: Integration test with password authentication\n  - Start Valkey with password\n  - Configure `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n  - Verify connection succeeds\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: Integration test with comma-separated addresses\n  - Configure `VALKEY_ADDR=\"addr1,addr2\"`\n  - Verify client connects to cluster\n\n### Phase 6: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add godoc comments to `valkeyStore` struct\n  - Document purpose and fields\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to `makeValkeyOptions()`\n  - Document all environment variables\n  - Document default values\n  - Document error conditions\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Add godoc comments to `NewValkeyStore()`\n  - Document parameters and return values\n\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Add godoc comments to all `valkeyStore` methods\n  - Document Valkey API patterns used\n  - Document DoMulti atomicity guarantees\n  - Document error conditions including `ErrNotFound`\n\n- [ ] **DOC-005**: Document key patterns in code comments\n  - `session:{id}` for JSON storage\n  - `session:expiry` ZSET for expiry index\n  - `session:last_activity` ZSET for activity index\n\n- [ ] **DOC-006**: Document ZSET score semantics\n  - Expiry score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n  - Last activity score = `LastActivityAt.Unix()` or `time.Now().Unix()`\n\n- [ ] **DOC-007**: Add code comment to `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()`\n  - Document MGET cluster slot consideration\n  - Note: \"Keys should be in same slot for cluster deployments\"\n\n- [ ] **DOC-008**: Document environment variables in code comments or README\n  - All `VALKEY_*` variables\n  - Default values and required status\n  - Case-insensitivity notes\n\n- [ ] **DOC-009**: Add example usage in doc.go or example test\n  - Initialize Valkey store via `NewValkeyStore()`\n  - Call `Ping()` to verify connectivity\n  - Call `StoreSandbox()` to persist sandbox\n  - Call `GetSandboxBySessionID()` to retrieve\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `valkeyStore` struct implements all `Store` interface methods\n- [ ] Key patterns match spec: `session:`, `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`\n- [ ] `DoMulti` operations used for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n- [ ] `ErrNotFound` returned consistently for missing sessions (via `IsValkeyNil`)\n- [ ] Environment variable parsing matches spec table\n- [ ] `makeValkeyOptions()` validates required fields and optional flags\n- [ ] `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` uses MGET optimization\n- [ ] MGET cluster slot consideration documented in code comment\n- [ ] All unit tests pass with mocked client\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for `store_valkey.go`\n- [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n- [ ] `Storage()` singleton supports `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | External | Valkey client library |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | `SandboxInfo` type |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types` | Internal | SandboxInfo alias source |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Internal | Store interface (AR-012) |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n```\nTASK-001\n    ↓\nTASK-010 → TASK-011\n    ↓\nTASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-022 → ... → TASK-028\n    ↓\nTASK-030\n    ↓\nTEST-001 → ... → TEST-040\n    ↓\nDOC-001 → ... → DOC-009\n```\n\n---\n\n## Related ARs\n\n| AR | Title | Relationship |\n|----|-------|--------------|\n| AR-012 | Session Storage Interface Definition | Base interface work |